These credentials are for local demo use only. Change passwords and secrets outside development.

## Authentication

Register or log in to receive JWT tokens, then send protected requests with:

```http
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```

Auth endpoints:

- `POST /api/auth/register/`
- `POST /api/auth/login/`
- `GET /api/auth/profile/`
- `PATCH /api/auth/profile/`
- `POST /api/auth/link-account/`
- `GET /api/auth/linked-accounts/`
- `POST /api/auth/switch/`

## Endpoint Map

- Health: `GET /api/health/`
- Projects: `GET|POST /api/projects/`, `GET|PATCH|DELETE /api/projects/{id}/`, `GET /api/projects/{id}/conversations/`
- Conversations: `GET|POST /api/conversations/`, `GET|PATCH|DELETE /api/conversations/{id}/`, `POST /api/conversations/{id}/archive/`, `POST /api/conversations/{id}/restore/`
- Conversation messages: `GET|POST /api/conversations/{id}/messages/`
- Messages: `PATCH|DELETE /api/messages/{id}/`, `GET /api/messages/{id}/attachments/`
- Attachments: `GET /api/attachments/{id}/download/`
- AI models: `GET /api/models/`, `GET /api/models/{id}/`, superuser `POST|PATCH|DELETE`
- Assistants: `GET|POST /api/assistants/`, `GET|PATCH|DELETE /api/assistants/{id}/`
- Subscription: `GET /api/subscription/plans/`, `GET /api/subscription/status/`, `POST /api/subscription/purchase/`
- Docs: `GET /api/schema/`, `GET /api/docs/`

## Notes And Limitations

- AI replies are deterministic mock responses. No external AI API is called.
- This is intentionally backend-only; no browser frontend is included.
- SQLite is the only configured database.
- Attachment storage and media serving are development-local. Protected downloads should use `/api/attachments/{id}/download/`.
- Every response includes `X-Request-ID`; structured API errors include the same request ID in the body.
